range vary with the size or typical use of the car; e.g., a subcompact car as compared to a large station wagon, or a car
typically used for city commuting compared to one used primarily for urban and intercity driving? Does the expected
driving range vary with the economic or social profile of the car operator; e.g., are younger drivers satisfied with
smaller ranges or do high-income drivers demand greater driving ranges? Would the consumer be willing to accept a
lower driving range in a vehicle with the added flexibility of dual fuel capability or with more recharging points
and shorter waiting times? What is the minimum driving range acceptable to consumers?
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
