that are likely to be affected, including officials from Massachusetts, Maine, and other states to develop a policy
to address this problem. This policy, described in a September 1, 1994 memorandum from Mary D. Nichols, Assistant
Administrator, to EPA regional offices, provides that states seeking to have the Clean Air Act interpreted so as to
allow them a later attainment deadline would have to make certain showings including a showing of overwhelming transport.
